metadata.name: On the sea, I ... #3
metadata.description:
Generative painting based on churning waves with floating buoys. Represented in three different media.

Features:
- Three drawing styles: "watercolor" 70%, "brush" 30%, or "block" 70%
- Warm white or blue waves
- Variable border and column sizes
- Number of columns
- Calm waves at the edges or center
- Color 80% or red 20% buoys
- Buoy drawing style, "watercolor" or "brush"

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.

metadata.name: Piastrelle #2
metadata.description:
Piastrelle is the Italian word for tiles, one of the oldest forms used for decorative art. They’ve been treasured for centuries due to their durability and stunning beauty, as embellishing touches both inside and outside of buildings of all types.

Examples of beautiful tile work can be found in mosaics, murals and more from the oldest civilizations to the present day. Ancient Egyptians, Assyrians, Babylonians, Chinese, Romans and Greeks favoured decorative tiles, and nowadays a wealth of amazing and varied floor and wall tile designs exist to suit all tastes.

This artwork attempts to dialogue with the ancient practice of tiles ornamentation, presenting fragments of tiled surfaces from an extinct civilization of the future, which once had their buildings decorated in all its glory.

Please be aware that there may be some pieces missing, not everything will stand the test of time.

Actions:

- [RETURN] saves current image
- [SPACE] saves large size image (7410 × 9880 px)

Remistura Studio, January 2022

metadata.name: de|growth:generations #121
metadata.description:
Materials tend to take particular forms due to their physical properties, technological necessities or natural limitations. However, what rules should a simulated environment follow when no physical constraints are inherent to the digital environment?

This project continues the exploration of shaping digital matter that I began on hicetnunc in 2021. Each token creates an image of a unique sculpture generated with a custom growth/degrowth algorithm. The image is rendered with a tailored raytracing script.

---
Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones for the 800x800px image.

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the resolution from preview quality to a print of approx. 30x30cm. There may be minor differences in tone or contrast for different resolutions.

In live mode:
Click PNG to save the rendered image.
Click STL to download the digital model to view on your computer or 3d print at home [experimental]

metadata.name: Boids 2D #9
metadata.description:
'Boids 2D' is a Generative Token that represent the flocking of birds over a landscape. The name 'Boids' comes from a famous computer animation / simulation program.

The landscape is rendered as a texture using a kind of warped noise as height map.

The boids are disposed along the flow lines obtained from the noise gradient. This gives the sensation that the Boids follow the undulations of the landscape.

Previously embedded in the 'Boids' (3D) Generative Token as an ester egg on 20% of iterations, now every iterations will be 2D as viewed from the sky.

Every owner of the 'Boids' (3D) GT will receive one 'Boids 2D' for free. The owner that minted a 'Boids' with ester egg will receive two 'Boids 2D' for free.

It is possible to save a 1600x1600 png with key 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- Noise warping control parameters generating different grade of complexity and different shape an the landscape and Boids flock (combined on a single number on the features).
- 21 color mapping for landscape and Boids.
- Two kind of border, solid or negative.

Features:
Palette: color palette name (21 different palettes)
NoiseControl: noise control parameter (0 - 15)
Border: the border can be in solid color or negative color (Solid, Negative)


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Perpetual Oscillations  #47
metadata.description:
Planes expand and contract over time in different rhythms. 

Display notes:
The work is intended to be viewed running live in the browser, and there is no set aspect ratio. The viewer is invited to explore the space and choose their viewpoint. 

Controls:
Left-clicking and dragging - rotate around the center 
right-clicking and dragging - pan around the space 
Scrolling - zoom in and out 
Press b - b-side 
Press o - go back to the origin 
Press 1 to 3 - change the pixel density
Adjusting pixel density or changing the screen size will bring you back to the origin. 

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Complicare #80
metadata.description:
Complicare is my first "still" generative work, and an exercise in minimalism.

Inspired by pioneers like Sol Lewitt and Frank Stella, as well as current fx_hash artists such as Rev Dan Catt and Yazid, this work attempts to balance a diverse visual output with a restricted generative system. I also wanted to focus on honing my abilities to add texture to the digital canvas, taking cues from other great artists on here like William Mapan and Hevey.

Each piece has one of 17 different layouts and one of 6 different color palettes.

Thanks to all of the artists on fx_hash for inspiring me every day to make more art, and particularly to dcarcher for some really insightful artistic perspective and feedback.

metadata.name: Divers N1 #9
metadata.description:
I remember holding my breath and sitting on the bottom of the public pool where I spent most summers. Every so often I would hear a sound like breaking glass played by a transistor radio  and turn see the form of a diver plunging into the deep end. 

Consider the form of a diver seconds after they hit water. I am struck the grace of a freefall, the shock of transition from air to water, and the shedding of bits the old world carried with the skin. 

Formally this piece is also my attempt to blend a kind of lyrical figurativism with the technical and aesthetic demands of long-form token based generative art. In this piece, a randomized subset of digitally sculpted  forms are loaded, spatially transformed via heuristics and RNG, and then translated into simple animated particle systems. 

This process of transformation occurs a variable number of times, so each piece could contain the base form of anywhere between 1 and 10 divers.

this piece was created with threejs

metadata.name: Cube City - Upside Down #13
metadata.description:
A generative cube city. 
Made in p5.js without webGL or any 3D library.
Arrange intensive cubes and strong colors to form interesting pictures.

Main variant is Type. 33% for a Upside Down city. 67% for a Normal.

Other variants:
2 patterns of Background (Stripe / Gradient)
2 patterns of Shadow (Homochromy / Contrast)
2 patterns of Cube Size (Large / Normal)
2 patterns of Stroke (Yes / No)
5 patterns of Fragment & 3 patterns of Stick Length.
And 24 selected Color Palettes.

Total 11,520 combinations.
All variants are selected and based on the balanced state between harmony and conflict.
